# Terraform working state — never commit these to the gitops repo.
**/.terraform/
**/.terraform.lock.hcl
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
# Plan artifacts produced in CI.
**/tfplan
**/plan.txt
**/plan.masked.txt

# GitOps exception: rendered deployment tfvars ARE the desired state and MUST be
# committed so CI can plan/apply them. If you initialize this repo with the stock
# Terraform .gitignore (which ignores *.tfvars), this negation re-includes the
# deployment inputs. They carry NO secrets — the master password is RDS-managed
# and IBM IDs are low-sensitivity.
!deployments/**/*.tfvars
